caption.body: SAS (Scandinavian Airlines System), the flag carrier for Norway, Denmark, and Sweden, was founded in 1951 after a merger of airlines from each country, Det Danske Luftfartselskab A/S (DDL), Det Norske Luftfartselskap A/S (DNL), and Svensk Interkontinetal Lufttrafik AB (SILA). The airline’s first international service departed from Stockholm to New York later that year and began promoting its service with posters highlighting the region’s attractions. SAS traces its linage to 1918 when Det Danske Luftfartselskab A/S (DDL) was founded. Have you ever flown on SAS?  poster: Scandinavian Airlines System (SAS), Copenhagen; 1960s Gift of Captain Jon Simmonds 2014.166.086 https://ow.ly/Wvim50R810p
